    "objective": "Synthesize the relationship between a specific renewable generation method and the primary high-voltage transmission level used for long-distance bulk transport.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "To move power from a large-scale source like an offshore wind farm to a distant city, the National Grid must use the highest available pressure to minimize energy wasted as heat.",
      "This process links the initial generation method directly to the transmission 'motorway' system, which operates at specific kilovolt (kV) levels.",
      "As an electrician, you must be able to identify the source of the power and the specific high-voltage level used for this primary transport phase."
    ],
    "questionText": "A large-scale offshore facility is generating electricity to be sent across the country. Identify the specific generation method used by this facility and state the highest UK transmission voltage (in kV) used for such primary long-distance bulk transport.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Wind and 400 kV",
      "Wind and 400kV",
      "Wind, 400 kV",
      "Wind, 400kV"
    ],
    "hint": "The generation method relates to the 'offshore' source, and the voltage is the highest of the three UK transmission levels (400, 275, or 132)."
  }
